      bio: { zh: '二十世紀中國最重要的小說家之一。生於上海沒落的官宦世家，作品多寫舊式家庭與都市男女的情感，筆下繁華而蒼涼。《半生緣》原以《十八春》之名於一九四八年連載，一九六八年大幅改寫定稿，是她少數以長篇篇幅寫盡「時間」與「錯過」的作品。她說過：因為懂得，所以慈悲。', en: 'One of the most important Chinese novelists of the twentieth century. Born into a declining mandarin family in Shanghai, she wrote of old households and the loves of city men and women — a world at once glittering and desolate. Half a Lifelong Romance was first serialized in 1948 as Eighteen Springs, then substantially rewritten in 1968 into its final form; it is one of her few full-length works to trace, at novel length, the workings of time and of missing one another. She once wrote: because one understands, one is merciful.' }
